></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526067\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526067\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bio1665702942630.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bio1665702942630.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bio1665702942630.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bio1665702942630\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      LDAP Data Structure\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bio1665702942630__ldap_data_structure_154028\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">LDAP data is stored in a record-like structure, called an entry. No table or field definition information is stored in the LDAP environment. Instead, each entry contains its own field definitions.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bio1665702942630__p_d51413e1_d51414e1_d51415e1\">All LDAP entries contain at least one object class field. Object classes are defined on the LDAP server as a set of mandatory and optional fields.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bio1665702942630__topic_d33797e1_d33798e1_d33799e1_d33800e1_d33801e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1218575e56\">\n                        \n Field Types\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bio1665702942630__p_d51419e1_d51420e1_d51421e1\">Object class definitions also specify the data type of each field. LDAP recognizes the following field types:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24467e1_d24468e1_d24469e1\">Single-value string fields (fixed length)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24470e1_d24471e1_d24472e1\">Multiple-value string fields (values are separated by a newline character)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24473e1_d24474e1_d24475e1\">Binary data fields\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bio1665702942630__topic_d33802e1_d33803e1_d33804e1_d33805e1_d33806e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1218575e77\">\n                        \n Tree Structure\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bio1665702942630__p_d51425e1_d51426e1_d51427e1\">LDAP organizes data into a hierarchical tree structure where each node in the tree represents an entry in a database. Entries correspond to a real-world object, that is, a person, department, organization, or country. They are collections of attribute-value pairs and are identified unambiguously by a distinguished name. A distinguished name is a combination of the entry name and the names of its parent entries, and is unique for all entries in a database. Typical attributes include the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24476e1_d24477e1_d24478e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">o</code>—organization\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24479e1_d24480e1_d24481e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ou</code>—organizational unit\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24482e1_d24483e1_d24484e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">c</code>—country\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24485e1_d24486e1_d24487e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">givenname</code>—given name\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24488e1_d24489e1_d24490e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">cn</code>—common name\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24491e1_d24492e1_d24493e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">email</code>—email address\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bio1665702942630__li_d24494e1_d24495e1_d24496e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">telephonenumber</code>—telephone number\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pfs1665702941848.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LDAP</a><p>The Lghtweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) is a protocol for accessing online directory services. It offers common access to a centralized facility for storing and maintaining user access privilege, email, and sign-on information which can be shared among Web servers, mail servers, news servers and Uniface applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aif1665702663917.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Storage and Retrieval on LDAP</a><p>LDAP differs substantially in structure from traditional relational databases.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526067\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526067\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "LDAP Data Structure Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 LDAP Data Structure LDAP data is stored in a record-like structure, called an entry. No table or field definition information is stored in the LDAP environment. Instead, each entry contains its own field definitions. All LDAP entries contain at least one object class field. Object classes are defined on the LDAP server as a set of mandatory and optional fields. Field Types Object class definitions also specify the data type of each field. LDAP recognizes the following field types: Single-value string fields (fixed length) Multiple-value string fields (values are separated by a newline character) Binary data fields Tree Structure LDAP organizes data into a hierarchical tree structure where each node in the tree represents an entry in a database. Entries correspond to a real-world object, that is, a person, department, organization, or country. They are collections of attribute-value pairs and are identified unambiguously by a distinguished name. A distinguished name is a combination of the entry name and the names of its parent entries, and is unique for all entries in a database. Typical attributes include the following: o —organization ou —organizational unit c —country givenname —given name cn —common name email —email address telephonenumber —telephone number Related Links LDAP The Lghtweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) is a protocol for accessing online directory services. It offers common access to a centralized facility for storing and maintaining user access privilege, email, and sign-on information which can be shared among Web servers, mail servers, news servers and Uniface applications. Data Storage and Retrieval on LDAP LDAP differs substantially in structure from traditional relational databases. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}